cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.AI. 

The paper presents a control strategy for dynamic legged locomotion in complex scenarios using a convolutional neural network and a model predictive controller. This involves robotics (cs.RO) and computer vision (cs.CV) techniques for terrain mapping and evaluation, as well as machine learning (cs.LG) for the neural network. The use of a predictive controller also suggests a systems and control (cs.SY) aspect to the paper. Finally, the optimization of ground reaction forces involves an element of artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
